  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Less oxidative stress occurs during off-pump than on-pump coronary artery bypass graft (CABG)
      surgery but warm ischaemia-reperfusion injury may occur following transient coronary artery
      clamping. The aim of this study was to compare the preventive effects of diltiazem and
      N-acetylcysteine (NAC), alone or in combination, on biomarkers of myocardial damage and
      oxidative stress during off-pump CABG surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
